feedback.answer: COULD have judged slightly better but overall nice
Feedback was insufficient, the feedback didn't make sense, and was confusing.
Very nice and provided GREAT feedback was very nice
The judge didn't give any credit to our responses or case. No alternative was given in the OA either.
Used judge's own knowledge to draw conclusions such as performing n independant stakeholder analysis. Not what was actually debated. Not quite happy about that on our end 😢
Very good feedback and clash analysis. W judge

We might be willing to accept the loss but not the reasons for the loss.
1. The adjudicator failed to give credit to thematic rebuttals brought out. 2. Bought way too much into side proposition and created a judging metric in which we have absolutely no chance to win. (If we were to accept their context, AI chatbots are the exact same thing as a normal relationships minus physical intimacy, which is extremely uncharitable.) 3. Only managed to identify 1 clash in a debate where atleast 2 to 3 clashes were talked about from both sides.
Good feedback and clash analysis. Very good judge
Decent feedback. Wasn't the best feedback as the judge had Internet issues so tracking speeches was difficult for them. Ok clash anylsis
Very Nice :D Obv DS A won, broke down feedback very well

Under the mercenary police model, local governments don't hire their own public police forces. Instead, they contract private security firms to perform police functions such as patrolling, investigation, and emergency response.

This House Would Live Like a Rolling Stone

"A rolling stone gathers no moss" is an idiom which suggests the benefit of living a life with no roots, frequently moving to different locations, and not tying yourself down.

In feminism, sorority is a concept that recognizes the importance of empathy, solidarity, and connection among women to confront patriarchal oppression and build networks of mutual support. In many contemporary practices, sorority is presented by imposing standards of conduct, loyalty, and forms of interaction on women, seeking specific behaviours and modes of belonging within the movement.
